article.description: — Sincere Carry matched his career high with a season-high 32 points as Kent State defeated Akron 67-55 on Friday night.
article.headline: Carry scores 32 to carry Kent St. past Akron 67-55
article.linkText: Carry scores 32 to carry Kent St. past Akron 67-55
article.story: KENT, Ohio -- — Sincere Carry matched his career high with a season-high 32 points as Kent State defeated Akron 67-55 on Friday night. Tervell Beck had 11 points for Kent State (8-8, 3-3 Mid-American Conference). Xavier Castaneda had 21 points for the Zips (9-5, 2-2). Enrique Freeman added 13 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
